de.oaam.model.oaam.common

Interface Integer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataTypeA, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IntegerImpl

    public interface Integer
extends DataTypeA
    A representation of the model object 'Integer'. A signed or unsigned integer of variable resolution.

    The following features are supported:

    • Signed
    • NBits
    • Endianess
    See Also:
    CommonPackage.getInteger()

        boolean isSigned()
        Returns the value of the 'Signed' attribute. The default value is "true". If the integer is signed it can hold also negative values. The default is true.

        int getNBits()
        Returns the value of the 'NBits' attribute. The default value is "16". The number of bits representing the integer. Common values are 8, 16, 32 and 64.
